<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="332" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d332">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.857Ar1/128</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the German Ambassador</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BJHACV1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bernstorff</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 1918</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1916</hi>
                                    </date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                                receipt of your note Nr. A 2346,<note n="1" xml:id="d332fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_222">p.
                                    222</ref>.</note> of April 2, 1916, in which you request a
                                statement as to what action this Government has taken or intends to
                                take with regard to the alleged misuse of the American flag by the
                                    <hi rend="italic">Baralong</hi> while firing on a German
                                submarine.</p>
                            <p>In reply I have the honor to inform your excellency that in view of
                                the fact that the statements made in the depositions received by the
                                Department in this case differ so materially in certain respects,
                                the Department has not felt warranted, on such contradictory
                                evidence, in taking up the matter with the British Government.</p>
                            <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>